    "description": "Free Humanoid Wheeled — sibling morphology to the Free Humanoid Platform (humanoid_bipedal), the centaur Free Humanoid Centaur (humanoid_quadruped), and the submersible Free Humanoid Submersible (humanoid_submersible). Targeted at the shoal dock-B service mission (urban stormwater outfalls, harbor docks, industrial discharge points — paved curb-edge dock service). Wheeled differential-drive base + tower stand + bipedal upper body inherited verbatim. ~70 kg total system, 2 kWh battery, 30 kg sustained payload at extended reach, 1.5 m/s peak speed, 600x800x350 mm base footprint, 15-inch pneumatic drive wheels. Drive actuator: QDD direct-drive into wheel hub via ~10:1 planetary reduction, T-Motor AK60-6 BLDC + mjbots Moteus n1 controllers (corpus: mit-cheetah-2 / mjbots-moteus). Tower stand: belt-driven linear stage (Igus DryLin SHTS-15 + NEMA-23 stepper, ±150 mm travel) per toyota-hsr telescoping-torso pattern. Outdoor sensing pinned to commercial-off-the-shelf SKUs: Livox MID-360 lidar (tower-top), u-blox ZED-F9P RTK GPS, VectorNav VN-100 IMU (production) or BNO055 (Phase 1 bench), Quectel RM502Q-AE 5G modem. Compute: NVIDIA Jetson Orin Nano Super 8GB (perception + planning) + Raspberry Pi 4 8GB (safety supervisor) on Simplex pattern. Battery: 24V 50Ah Li-ion AGV-class pack (~1.2 kWh shown at 24V; descriptor still nominally 2 kWh @ 48V via dual modules — Phase 2 picks the final cell-and-bus voltage). Frame: 6061-T6 aluminum monocoque + 3D-printed PA12 covers. Upper body actuator distribution inherited from bipedal sibling (corpus: honda-e0 harmonic-drive at shoulder/elbow, shadow-dexterous-hand tendon at wrist/hand, pisa-iit-softhand at synergy hand, mini-cheetah QDD at neck/waist). Safety supervisor: MathGround-style Simplex (corpus: sherman-simplex-architecture, control-barrier-functions) plus wheeled-specific invariants (slope-tilt, edge-proximity, low-battery-on-shore-power). Mission integration with shoal dock-B (cartridge-swap, waste-hopper, biology-reservoir handshake, water-utility EAM). Compiles to URDF / MJCF / STL / BOM via the OpenLoco descriptor compiler. All masses and inertias are scaffold placeholders for now — iterate against physical CAD before any build; Phase 1 numbers are derived from vendor data sheets + reasonable structural estimates.",
